From: Blakestream-GaintB <sid@blakestream.local>
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] driver-baikalu: don't nuke whole device on single miner send_work failure

Part 2 of the ascdisable deadlock fix.

baikal_update_work() called baikal_cleanup(baikal) when baikal_send_work
failed for ANY individual miner. baikal_cleanup() is the nuclear option:
it iterates over all miners on the device, sets shutdown=true and
deven=DEV_DISABLED for each, and disconnects USB. Wildly disproportionate
to a single miner's queue being full.

Replace with a localized log + skip for that miner this round. The next
block change will try again. If it's a transient queue full, it recovers.
If it's persistent (e.g. miner physically disconnected), the existing
sgminer health-monitoring loop will detect it via missing scanhash
results and mark just that one miner unhealthy.
---
 driver-baikalu.c | 6 ++++--
 1 file changed, 4 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/driver-baikalu.c b/driver-baikalu.c
--- a/driver-baikalu.c
+++ b/driver-baikalu.c
@@ -897,8 +897,10 @@ static void baikal_update_work(struct cgpu_info *baikal)

             for (j = 0; j < count; j++) {
                 if (baikal_send_work(baikal, i) != true) {
-                    baikal_cleanup(baikal);
-                    break;
+                    applog(LOG_WARNING,
+                           "baikal_send_work failed for miner %d, skipping this round (was: full device cleanup)",
+                           i);
+                    break;  /* skip remaining sends to this miner this round, don't nuke other miners */
                 }
             }
         }
